caption: One of the good location in paris for insta photo lovers. The magic starts from the pink building and it covers the whole rue with colourful buildings. Free of cost ‚úÖ Easy transport‚úÖ Less crowded on weekdays ‚úÖ

This is definitely a must visit place in Paris I reckon. A Colourful Piece of Paradise in Paris:  Rue Cremieux Paris in the 12th Arrondissement is a place of pastel coloured houses and shutters, a quirky little street in the centre of the city‚Ä¶

Nothing really cultural about the place. There wasn‚Äôt much to read up about as well.  But this place was really gorgeous to just be around and admire. The colourful buildings is not something I see often. Decent place for a photoshoot!

A wonderful place to wonder into and take some dope pics of outfits/selfies, in fact there are more fashion bloggers here than in most parisian places I've visited! Better in the early morning/late afternoon, when the light is not too strong.
Lovely colourful little street, well worth a visit, best on a sunny day.

Beautiful and cute place. Since, it's a regular street, tourists are very welcomed there. Good to stay some minutes and take a couple of pics. In respect of the people there, stay quite and don't mess it up
Totally Instaworthy! Mostly filled with young women taking posed pictures but the colours were beautiful and worth strolling down if you're in the area.

A bit of color in light browny-creamy white Paris. Recommend for a change in scenery and having another snapshot in this city.  I can't say I was really impressed (at least not as much as with La Bute aux Cailles). Beauty still lies in the eye of the beholder (or the way you use your camera, that is).
A small street in Paris with 30..20 colorful houses. I liked it. It is more beautiful in pictures üòÅ ‚Ä¶
Nice to visit; But, it worth to visit if you would like to take a few photos of those colorful houses, that's all.
It's a very cute street with beautiful colors. But dont make the trip just to see it. It's only a few dozen houses.

Giving it a 1 star just to bring down the overall rating in the hope that (foreign) tourists respect the fact that the houses here are private homes and they should respect the signs and NOT TAKE PHOTOS OR VIDEOS! Anyway the buildings have lost their original colour and shine so only filters would make the (forbidden) photos look good. The street is nicely maintained though and it feels nice to walk through it, if only to find out what all the hype is about!
Really cool looking, but I sure would hate to live there. Lots of folks walking through.

Beautiful street near Gare du Lyon. Lovely pastel facades,  some with added artwork and details. However, I can imagine that might be a bit annoying having tourists - like us - hanging out taking pictures. Perhaps it's better just to take a quick stroll through and enjoy it,  then move on.

Beautiful colours, no pictures here that's a shame. Yet it is also a very quiet place in this busy Metropole. Yet I like also the cosyambiance being created with press and plants and the bicycles against the walls.

Go there when there is light, when the weather is sunny, you will get good photos. We went there when it was cloudy. We didn't get amazing pictures but it was worth visiting. Note: The neighborhood doesn't appreciate you clicking pictures over there.

Not at it's best in winter. Best visited on sunny days. Not posting photo out of respect to the neighborhood, didnt stop me from clicking one though. Cool street
Supposedly instagram famous. The locals don't like attention so be polite and descrete when taking pictures. Some houses forbid you to take pictures of them.
One of the most picturesque places in Paris. Beware that a few tenants won't allow you to take pictures in front of their door.
A highly photographed Instagram hotspot, which is probably why the residents politely request that you don‚Äôt take photos.
Very nice place. Perfect to take a photo but it will be feel uncomfortable to the neighborhood. Igual, I took many pictures too üòÑ ‚Ä¶
It's pretty, but the owners aren't very nice, which is understandable considering hundreds of tourists stroll in front of their homes everyday.
A small calm street!
Isn't worth the detour if you're coming in this area just for this little street, as there's nothing much around. The street is too narrow it's hard to get a nice photo.
It is a street of Paris thats takes you back to the 1950s. Small authentic townhouses painted with pastel colours. Gorgeous place.
Beautiful place to visit. Just be sure to be respectful of the residents, so they don't block it for future visitors.
Few colorfully painted houses. Rather unusual in Paris, worth a short trip. One house has a sign on front door: "no photos" :)
A must see for any tourists to Paris! A beautiful street with lots of colorful apartments - a very Instagramable street ;)
A nice street in paris near gare de lyon. If you want take pics so i recommend you go there at afternoon.
A colorful part of Paris !
Beautiful place but you cant take picture according to signs out there.
Nice colorful houses but always have people there so you need to find the time that not many people
Leave the people living here alone and please don't go with your stupid cameras..
Nice place for a walk. It is a short street with colorful buildings.
Nice street with the colorfull houses. The colors have faded so its not as bright as it seems
Touristic Instagram influencer must see for masses. If that's not you give it a miss darlings.
You have to wait a long time for the perfect picture, because there are always people walking by
